Function compileScript

system.engine compileScript (script )

Compile the "script" string to bytecode

Function defineProperty

system.engine defineProperty (object, key, descriptor )

Define a property on the object with the enumerable, writable, and deletable fields set as in the descriptor object. Very similar to the proposal for ECMAScript 3.1 Object.defineProperty, this will hopefully be made obsolete soon.

Function freezeObject

system.engine freezeObject (obj )

Make an object entirely read-only. New properties cannot be added, and existing properties are set to {deletable:false, writable:false}

Function getPropertyDefinition

system.engine getPropertyDefinition (object, property )

Return a property descriptor object for the property specified.

Function getState

system.engine getState ( )

Returns a representation of the current state of the virtual machine

Function runScript

system.engine runScript (script, bytecode )

Just like the traditional eval function, but it can take a second argument to aid in compilation and speed things up a bit.

Function sealObject

system.engine sealObject (obj )

Make an object non-dynamic. New properties cannot be added, and existing properties are set to {deletable:false}

Function setState

system.engine setState (state )

Set the state of the virtual machine to the state represented by the "state" argument

Module system.engine

Undocumented

Function fclose

system.posix fclose (file )

Closes the given file object.

Function fopen

system.posix fopen (path, mode )

Opens the file at the given path using the given mode. This returns a file object, that you should not forget to close.

 var fd = fopen("/tmp/myfile.txt", "w")

Function fread

system.posix fread (file, size, quantity )

Reads quantity elements of the given size (in bytes) from the given file object, returning a string which may be emty if there is nothing to be read.

Function pclose

system.posix pclose (file )

Closes the file object that was previously created with the popen function.

Function popen

system.posix popen (command, type )

Opens a process with the given command and returns a file object to which you can read or write, depending on the type argument (r or w)

 var fd = popen("echo Hello !", "r")

Function system

system.posix system (command )

Executes the given system commands and returns an integer representing the STATUS of the command.

Function time

system.posix time ( )

Returns the local UNIX time as an integer, in milliseconds
